{"title_page": "Abdulaziz al-Tarefe", "text_new": "{{short description|21st-century Islamic cleric}}{{Infobox religious biography|religion=[[Islam]]\n|name = Abd Al-Aziz al-Tarefe\n|native_name = {{lang|ar|\u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a}}\n|native_name_lang = \n|image = \n|alt = \n|denomination = [[Sunni]]\n|jurisprudence = [[Hanbali]]\n|creed = [[Athari]]\n|movement = [[Salafi]]\n|notable_ideas = \n|influences = [[Ibn Taymiyyah]], [[Ibn al-Qayyim]], [[Muhammad Ibn Abd al-Wahhab]], [[Abd al-Aziz ibn Baz]], [[Muhammad ibn al Uthaymeen]]\n|influenced = \n|post = \n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1976|11|29}}\n|birth_place = [[Kuwait]]\n|death_date = \n|death_place = \n|alma_mater =  [[Imam Muhammad ibn Saud Islamic University]]\n|website = \n}}\n\n'''Abdulaziz al-Tarefe (''' [[Arabic]] \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a)  ( born in 29 November ,1976 in [[Kuwait]] ) is a [[Saudi Arabia|Saudi Arabian]] Islamic [[Scholar]] \n\nAl-Tarefe is a Sunni scholar who is known for his knowledge in [[Hadith]] and [[Fiqh]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.aljazeera.net/blogs/2019/1/5/\u0639\u0628\u062f-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632-\u0627\u0644\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a-\u0642\u0635\u0629-\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0645-\u062d\u0631\u0645\u062a-\u0645\u0646\u0647-\u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0629|title=\u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a.. \u0642\u0635\u0629 \u0639\u0627\u0644\u0645 \u062d\u064f\u0631\u0645\u062a \u0645\u0646\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0629|website=blogs.aljazeera.net|language=ar|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/politics/2019/10/1/\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f\u064a\u0629-\u0646\u0642\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u0634\u064a\u062e-\u0627\u0644\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a-\u0644\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0634\u0641\u06