hout Pity]]''\n| Sgt. Kelly Harris\n|Television film\n|-\n|2002\n| ''[[Charmed]]'' \n| Karen Young\n|Episode: \"The Fifth Halliwell\"\n|-\n|2002\n| ''[[Friends]]'' \n| Sarah\n|Episode: \"The One with the Cooking Class\"\n|-\n|2002\n| ''[[Greetings from Tucson]]'' \n| Karen Tobin\n|Recurring role, 3 episodes\n|-\n|2003\n| ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'' \n| Rachel\n|Episode: \"Tears, Bones & Desire\"\n|-\n|2003\n| ''[[The Agency (2001 TV series)|The Agency]]'' \n| Caroline Magnuson\n|Episode: \"Our Man in Korea\"\n|-\n|2003\n| ''[[NYPD Blue]]'' \n| Nancy Ackerman \n|Episodes: \"Keeping Abreast\" and \"Andy Appleseed\"\n|-\n|2004\n| ''[[JAG (TV series)|JAG]]'' \n| Navy Captain\n|Episode: \"Take It Like a Man\"\n|-\n|2004\n| ''[[Monk (TV series)|Monk]]'' \n| Ms. Lennington\n|Episode: \"Mr. Monk Gets Fired\"\n|-\n|2005\n| ''[[Numbers (TV series)|Numb3rs]]'' \n| Fingerprint Technician\n|Episode: \"Identity Crisis\"\n|-\n|2005\n| ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'' \n| Audrey Vetter\n|Episode: \"Conspiracy Theory\"\n|-\n|2005\n| ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'' \n| Meredith Smart\n|Episode: \"Carter est Amoureux\"\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Murder 101 (film series)|Murder 101: College Can Be Murder]]''\n| Hilda Lake\n|Television film\n|-\n|2007\n| ''[[The Closer]]'' \n| Kathy Reichter\n|Episode: \"Homewrecker\"\n|-\n|2007\n| ''[[Side Order of Life]]'' \n| Karma\n|Episode: \"When Pigs Fly\"\n|-\n|2007\n| ''[[Private Practice (TV series)|Private Practice]]'' \n| Karen Adams\n|Episode: \"In Which Addison Finds the Magic\"\n|-\n|2004\u20132007\n| ''[[Unfabulous]] '' \n| Sue Singer\n|Series regular, 29 episodes\n|-\n|2008\n| ''[[Eli Stone]]'' \n| Moira Foote\n|Episode: \"Waiting for That Day\"\n|-\n|2008\n| ''[[Cold Case]]'' \n| Lois Rabinski\n|Episode: \"Ghost of My Child\"\n|-\n|2008\n| ''[[Fear Itself (TV series)|Fear Itself]] '' \n| Elena Edlund\n|Episode: \"Skin and Bones\"\n|-\n|2008\n| ''[[Ghost Whisperer]]'' \n| Penny Jones\n|Episode: \"Ghost in the Machine\"\n|-\n|2008\n| ''[[Bones (TV series)|Bones]]'' \n| Elsbeth King\n|Episode: \"The Bone That Blew\"\n|-\n|2009\n| ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' \n| Jackie\n|Episode: \"Elevator Love Letter\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Princess Protection Program]] ''\n| The Director\n|Television film\n|-\n|2009\n| ''[[Medium (TV series)|Medium]]'' \n| E.R. Doctor\n|Episode: \"Bite Me\"\n|-\n|2011\n| ''[[CHAOS (TV series)|Chaos]]'' \n| Ms. Lurkin\n|Episodes: \"Pilot\" and \"Mol\u00e9\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Cinema Verite]]''\n| Kaye\n|Television film\n|-\n|2012\n| ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'' \n| Gillian\n|Episode: \"Any Moment\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[TalhotBlond (2012 film)|TalhotBlond]]''\n| Beth Brooks\n|Television film\n|-\n|2012\n| ''[[Perception (American TV series)|Perception]]'' \n| Professor\n|Episode: \"Kilimanjaro\"\n|-\n|2013\n| ''[[The Mentalist]]'' \n| Elizabeth Hennings\n|Episode: \"Red Velvet Cupcakes\"\n|-\n|2013\n| ''[[NCIS: Los Angeles]]'' \n| Peggy Winant\n|Episode: \"Recovery\"\n|-\n|2013\n| ''[[Masters of Sex]]'' \n| Sybil\n|Episode: \"Fallout\"\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[Liv and Maddie]]'' \n| Mrs. Wakefield\n|Episode: \"Moms-a-Rooney\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Petals on the Wind (film)|Petals on the Wind]]''\n| Miss Calhoun\n|Television film\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[Longmire (TV series)|Longmire]]'' \n| Sylvia Mallory\n|Episode: \"Miss Cheyenne\"\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[Switched at Birth (TV series)|Switched at Birth]]'' \n| Tammy Brenawicz\n|Episode: \"And We Bring the Light\"\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[Stalker (TV series)|Stalker]]'' \n|Nancy Dalton\n|Episode: \"Fanatic\"\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[Rectify]]'' \n| \n|Episode: \"Donald the Normal\"\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[Castle (TV series)|Castle]]'' \n| Daisy May\n|Episode: \"Once Upon a Time in the West\"\n|-\n|2014\u20132015\n| ''[[Instant Mom]]'' \n| Eunice Ebnetter\n|Recurring role, 3 episodes\n|-\n|2015, 2019 \n| ''[[IZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]'' \n| Eva Moore\n|Recurring role, 7 episodes\n|-\n|2015\n| ''[[True Detective (TV series)|True Detective]]'' \n| Mrs. Harris\n|Episodes: \"The Western Book of the Dead\" and \"Other Lives\"\n|-\n|2015\n| ''A Teacher's Obsession''\n|Candace\n| Television Film\n|-\n|2016\u20132019\n| ''[[Jane the Virgin]]'' \n| Patricia Cordero\n|Recurring role, 7 episodes\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[NCIS: New Orleans]]''\n|Elaine Jarrett\n|Episode: \"Help Wanted\"\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Mistresses (American TV series)|Mistresses]]''\n|Dr. Paysinger\n|Episode: \"Under Pressure\"\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Dead of Summer (TV series)|Dead of Summer]]''\n|Beth Dalton\n|Episode: \"Modern Love\"\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[This Is Us]]''\n|Grace\n|Episode: \"Career Days\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Better Call Saul]]''\n|Judge Lindsay Arch\n|Episode: \"Sunk Costs\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Feud (TV series)|Feud]]''\n|Bette's Doctor\n|Episode: \"You Mean All This Time We Could Have Been Friends?\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]''\n|Dr. Moriarty\n|Recurring role, 2 episodes\n|-\n|2017\n| ''[[Law & Order True Crime]]''\n|Joan Vandermolen\n|Recurring role, 7 episodes\n|-\n|2017\u20132019\n|''[[The Orville]]''\n|Drenala Kitan\n|Recurring role, 2 episodes: \"Firestorm\", \"Home\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Legion (TV series)|Legion]]''\n|Laura Mercer\n|Episode: \"Chapter 14\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Reverie (TV series)|Reverie]]''\n|Tirzah Hagan\n|Episodes: \"Point of Origin\" and \"The Key\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''Long Lost Daughter''\n|Kathy Rhodes\n|Television film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[How to Get Away with Murder]]''\n|A.D.A. Nancy Montoya\n|Episode: \"Whose Blood Is That?\"\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[No Good Nick]]''\n|Dorothy\n|Recurring role, 9 episodes \n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Into the Dark (TV series)|Into the Dark]]''\n|Kiwi\n|Episode: \"A Nasty Piece of Work\"\n|-\n|2019-2020\n|''[[Truth Be Told (2019 TV series)|Truth Be Told]]''\n|Susan Carver\n|Recurring role, 4 episodes\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Narcos: Mexico]]''\n|Stella Mancuso\n|Episode: \"The Big Dig\"\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Walker, Texas Ranger]]''\n|Abeline Walker\n|Series regular\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://mollyhagan.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|353243}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hagan, Molly}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Minneapolis]]\n[[Category:American soap opera actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Northwestern University School of Communication alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Molly Hagan\n|image =\n|imagesize = \n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1961|8|3|mf=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Minneapolis]], [[Minnesota]], U.S\n|years_active = 1985&ndash;present\n|occupation = Actress\n|spouse = \n|website = https://mollyhagan.com/}}\n\n'''Molly Joan Hagan''' (born August 3, 1961) is an American actress. She co-starred in films ''[[Code of Silence (1985 film)|Code of Silence]]'' (1985), ''[[Some Kind of Wonderful (film)|Some Kind of Wonderful]]'' (1987), ''[[The Dentist]]'' (1996), ''[[Election (1999 film)|Election]]'' (1999) and ''[[Sully (film)|Sully]]'' (2016), and is also known for her roles in television on ''[[Herman's Head]]'' (1991\u20131994) and ''[[Unfabulous]]'' (2004\u20132007).\n\n==Life and career==\nHagan was born in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]],<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web | url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/29538/Molly-Hagen/biography | title=Molly Hagen Biography | publisher=[[The New York Times]] | accessdate=March 27, 2013}}</ref> the daughter of Mary Elizabeth ([[married and maiden names|n\u00e9e]] Henslee) and John Robert Hagan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/22/Molly-Hagan.html|title=Molly Hagan Biography (1961-)|website=www.filmreference.com}}</ref> She was raised in [[Fort Wayne, Indiana]] and attended [[Northwestern University]].<ref name=\"bio\" />\n\nHagan played Diana Luna alongside [[Chuck Norris]] on the 1985 action film ''[[Code of Silence (1985 film)|Code of Silence]]''. Hagan has made appearances in films such as ''[[Some Kind of Wonderful (film)|Some Kind of Wonderful]]'' and most notably as the young [[Miss Ellie Ewing]] in the television movie ''[[Dallas: The Early Years]]''<ref name=\"bio\"/> (a prequel of the long-running soap opera ''[[Dallas (1978 TV series)|Dallas]]'') and she has appeared in several other television series, including the 1980s situation comedy ''[[The Golden Girls]]'' as Caroline, the daughter of Miles Webber, Rose's romantic partner.\n\nHagan starred in the cult series ''[[Nutt House]]'', which had a six-week run in 1989, and ''[[Herman's Head]]'' which ran on Fox from 1991 to 1994. She portrayed Angel, one of the four characters inside Herman, and represented his sensitivity. She was in two episodes of the detective mystery series ''[[Columbo]]'', namely ''[[List of Columbo episodes#Season 8|Murder, Smoke and Shadows]]'' (1989), and ''[[List of Columbo episodes#Season 10 and specials|Butterfly in Shades of Grey]]'' (1994). She also appeared twice on ''[[Murder, She Wrote]]'' (in two different roles). In the end of the second season of ''[[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine]]'', she played a young Vorta called Eris in \"[[The Jem'Hadar]]\". She appeared in three episodes of the third season of ''[[Becker (TV series)|Becker]]'', she also appeared on ''[[Seinfeld]]'' as Sister Roberta, the Latvian Orthodox novice that Kramer nearly took from the church, and a cooking teacher on ''[[Friends]]''. She played a trailer trash mother in a Jerry Springer-based movie, ''Ringmaster''. She played Diane McAllister in the 1999 movie ''[[Election (1999 film)|Election]]'' opposite [[Matthew Broderick]]. Hagan also played Coach Crenshaw in ''[[Air Bud: Seventh Inning Fetch]]''.\n\nHagan played the mother of [[Emma Roberts]]'s character Addie in the [[Nickelodeon]] series ''[[Unfabulous]]'' from 2004 to 2007. She also made a guest appearances in many television series, such as ''[[Charmed]]'', ''[[Bones (TV series)|Bones]]'', ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'', ''[[Ghost Whisperer]]'', ''[[Cold Case]]'', ''[[Private Practice (TV series)|Private Practice]]'', ''[[The Closer]]'', and ''[[NYPD Blue]]''. Hagan also appeared in [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Princess Protection Program]]'' in 2009, and had another guest appearance in an episode of the Disney Channel sitcom ''[[Liv and Maddie]]''. In 2014, Hagan was cast as the lead character's mother in [[The CW]] series, ''[[IZombie (TV series)|IZombie]]'', based on the DC Comics.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/08/20/izombie-molly-hagan-judy-reyes/ | title='iZombie' recasts mom, adds 'Devious Maids' star | publisher=Entertainment Weekly | date=August 20, 2014 | accessdate=21 August 2014 | author=Natalie Abrams}}</ref> She later made recurring guest appearances in ''[[Jane the Virgin]]'' and ''[[The Orville]]'', ''[[No Good Nick]]'' and ''[[Truth Be Told (2019 TV series)|Truth Be Told]]''. In 2017 she co-starred in the NBC limited series ''[[Law & Order True Crime]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/law-order-true-crime-the-menendez-murders-sterling-beaumon-molly-hagan-dominic-flores-cast-1202114499/|title=\u2018Law & Order True Crime: The Menendez Murders\u2019: Sterling Beaumon, Molly Hagan & Dominic Flores Join Cast|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|date=June 15, 2017}}</ref> and in 2020 was cast in a series regular role as title character mother in the CW crime series, ''[[Walker, Texas Ranger]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/molly-hagan-the-cw-walker-texas-ranger-reboot-1202869991/|title=Molly Hagan To Co-Star In The CW\u2019s \u2018Walker, Texas Ranger\u2019 Reboot|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|date=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[C